https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/eavzpmj9gXSg4IuCq8nqCOTK0uX.jpg The rock and roll at the State of Mexico comes alive with the participation of several dozen musical groups, ranging from small auditions in wastelands and warehouses to large productions with massive events, with five or ten thousand people. In this universe of rituals, symbols and codes, we approach the work of eight bands: Bostik, Tex tex, Liran'roll, Lvzbel, Rebel'd Punk, Follaje blues band, Transmetal, and Juan Hernandez and his blues band. At The Outskirts
